  [2]: https://sourceforge.net/projects/sigar/files/
  [3]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12214114/how-to-include-sigar-api-in-java-project

It seems [Sigar][1] mentioned in another answer is no longer maintained and does not work with recent Windows versions because of 64b/32b incompatibilites (see [PR 142][2]).

There seems to be another library for the purposes, which seems to be alive (last version published a few days ago) [OSHI][3].

With OSHI you can get the information like this:

```
SystemInfo si = new SystemInfo();
HardwareAbstractionLayer hal = si.getHardware();
CentralProcessor cpu = hal.getProcessor();
String name = cpu.getProcessorIdentifier().getName();
```



